M|Key |**Be|**
M|Key |it|[ ] Payback period <6 months (w/ annual upfront)
M|Key |it|[ ] 80%+ of deals on annual payment terms
M|Key |it|[ ] Runway >18 months
M|Key |- [ |1 (sustainable growth)
M|Key |it|[ ] Sales cycle <4 months
M|Key |**We|**
M|Key |it|[ ] Cash balance
M|Key |it|[ ] Weekly burn rate
M|Key |it|[ ] Weeks of runway remaining
M|Key |it|[ ] New bookings (cash collected, not just ARR)
M|Key |tx|---
M|Key |**LT|CAC ratio is necessary but not sufficient.**
M|Key |This|
M|Key |- ✅ |CAC (5:1)
M|Key |it|✅ Strong gross margin (85%)
M|Key |it|✅ Good retention (4+ year lifetime)
M|Key |But |
M|Key |it|🚨 18-month effective payback (6-month sales cycle + 11-month cash recovery)
M|Key |it|🚨 Quarterly billing (delays cash)
M|Key |it|🚨 11-month runway (insufficient for sales cycle + payback)
M|Key |**Th|** Negotiate annual upfront payments. This turns an 11-month payback into a <1-month payback, unlocking sustainable scaling.
M|Key |**Le|** Always pair LTV:CAC w/ payback period AND cash collection timing. Otherwise, you'll scale yourself into bankruptcy while the metrics look great on paper.